The man pauses, looking thoughtfully at the page. He sighs, signing the letter and putting down his pen before 
folding the letter and placing it neatly in the envolope.

The envolope is made of meat. What else?
After all, this was Chinatown.

Hours later. Long after the envolope had made its way across town. Two salesmen working for Johnstone's Deep Insurance 
were pounding on the door. It reverbed like a whip in the loving carress of a young Harrison Ford. No door could withstand such for long.
They stepped over the debris, torches sweeping the room. After some minutes silent sifting a swab was made of faint pink residue on the desk.

